The paper deals with modelling long-range dependencies in computer vision tasks such as semantic segmentation and object detection, which are typically categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The proposed method involves a message passing neural network framework, which is a popular approach in the fields of machine learning and artificial intelligence, hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The method also involves dynamically predicting node-dependent filter weights and affinity matrix, which are common techniques in neural network architectures, hence cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category. Finally, the paper also mentions the use of natural language processing techniques for text-based tasks, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
